<br>
I belive the aaxp actually kicks in under weight but don't have a high level test character to test it out. It is programmed / moved to be there.<br>
<br>
Once this goes live I will probably move the text down to place the aaxp bar under the normal exp bar.<br>
<br>
As to learing how to do it....for the stuff that I have done its been pretty easy. Most of it is just figuring out where the x,y coordinates of a particular box goes and then changing it in the file to move it into the new position.<br>
<br>
I create a mock up in photoshop of the size i want then cut and paste the parts in from verants art files in the default skins directory. Once they are moved into place I use the measure tool to figure out its x,y placement of an element. Most other elements are based off that one.<br>
<br>
For example the top left earring is something like 28 pixles in from the far left side and 2 pixles from the very top of the window. From that I know that all the others are going to be 40 pixles to the right because that is the size verant has for the default equipment boxes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   so the neck is 68,2 and the face is 102,2 etc...<br>
<br>
Then you load the skin up and see if you messed up somewhere. Take a screenshot and see what element is out of place and where it should be, then just change the xml file and try again.<br>
<br>
I am currently working on a mod for the hotbuttons area but its a little beyond my expertise, not being an actual xml programmer so either i read some tut sites or get some help from some people who are better at this then me.<br>
<br>
The mod will be very useful I think to magicians in general <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
